            "list": [
              {
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/19/94376896/d802b2ddce3781170a16c7834e5d837f_3684380279868925784.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>A weapon that mostly appears near sunken ships. When a character appears within its line of sight and attack range, it will <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">lock on and attack</span>.</p>",
                "key": "Page 1/2"
              },
              {
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2023/12/19/94376896/ae871fc5c8bd8cd7bd76e6858067f715_2551549593570277179.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>In most circumstances, you can follow the energy flow to find the missing crystal <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">\"receiver nodes\"</span> for the autocannons. After <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">inserting</span> the nodes into the ship's cannons, and by continually <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">releasing Xenochromatic Ball Octopus energy</span> at them, the ship's autocannon <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">control permissions</span> can be overridden. It will then cease attacking characters and can be manually controlled.</p>",
                "key": "Page 2/2"
              }
            ],
